Alembic environment for TENANT schemas.

Manages per-tenant tables (users, employees, jobs, applications, leave_*, etc.)
declared on TenantBase. Each tenant lives in its own PostgreSQL schema and
tracks its own alembic_version row.

Single-tenant commands (run from repo root):

  # Generate a new migration by diffing TenantBase models against one tenant
  alembic -c alembic_tenant.ini -x tenant=<tenant_id> revision \
      --autogenerate -m "describe the change"

  # Apply migrations to one tenant
  alembic -c alembic_tenant.ini -x tenant=<tenant_id> upgrade head

  # Roll back
  alembic -c alembic_tenant.ini -x tenant=<tenant_id> downgrade -1

  # Current revision for one tenant
  alembic -c alembic_tenant.ini -x tenant=<tenant_id> current

All-tenant commands (apply across every tenant in public.clients):

  python scripts/tenant_migrate.py upgrade head
  python scripts/tenant_migrate.py downgrade -1
  python scripts/tenant_migrate.py current
  python scripts/tenant_migrate.py stamp head
  python scripts/tenant_migrate.py upgrade head --tenant acme   # one tenant

Notes:
  - The version table lives at <tenant_id>.alembic_version.
  - --autogenerate should be run against ONE representative tenant (one whose
    schema matches the model state you want to diff against), then the
    generated migration is applied to every tenant.
